---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageSchema = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Glass Curtains Estepona",
  "description": "Glass curtain installation in Estepona. Costa Glass is based in Estepona and serves all local residential and commercial projects.",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Costa Glass",
    "telephone": "+34951074067",
    "url": "https://costaglass.com",
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "streetAddress": "Calle el Cerrillo, Nave 6",
      "addressLocality": "Estepona",
      "addressRegion": "Málaga",
      "postalCode": "29680",
      "addressCountry": "ES"
    }
  },
  "areaServed": { "@type": "City", "name": "Estepona" },
  "url": "https://costaglass.com/en/glass-installation-estepona/"
});
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Glass Curtains Estepona | Local Manufacturer & Installer | Costa Glass"
  description="Glass curtains in Estepona installed by Costa Glass — the local manufacturer based in Estepona. Fast installation, no middlemen, competitive direct-factory prices."
  canonical="https://costaglass.com/en/glass-installation-estepona/"
  ogImage="https://costaglass.com/Assets/products/glass curtain walls/c3.jpg"
  pageSchema={pageSchema}
  lang="en"
>

<style>
  .en-hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #0c4a6e 100%); color: white; padding: 100px 20px 80px; text-align: center; }
  .en-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); margin: 0 0 20px; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
  .en-hero p { font-size: 1.2rem; max-width: 650px; margin: 0 auto 32px; opacity: 0.9; }
  .en-badge { display: inline-block; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); border-radius: 30px; padding: 6px 20px; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .en-section { padding: 70px 20px; }
  .en-section:nth-child(even) { background: #f8fafc; }
  .en-container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .en-section h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); color: #0f172a; margin: 0 0 24px; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
  .en-section p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #374151; margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .advantage-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 24px 0; }
  .advantage-list li { display: flex; gap: 12px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9; align-items: flex-start; }
  .advantage-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .advantage-list .icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .advantage-list .text strong { display: block; font-size: 1rem; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .advantage-list .text p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #475569; }
  .cta-band { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0284c7, #0ea5e9); color: white; padding: 60px 20px; text-align: center; }
  .cta-band h2 { font-size: 2rem; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .cta-band p { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 28px; opacity: 0.95; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .btn-white { display: inline-block; background: white; color: #0284c7; padding: 14px 32px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; }
  .btn-white:hover { background: #f0f9ff; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 20px 0 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; }
  .related-links a { display: inline-block; background: #e0f2fe; color: #0284c7; padding: 8px 18px; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .info-strip { background: #0f172a; color: white; padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; margin: 28px 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; }
  .info-strip-item h3 { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #94a3b8; margin: 0 0 6px; }
  .info-strip-item p { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin: 0; }
</style>

<section class="en-hero">
  <div class="en-container">
    <span class="en-badge">Based in Estepona — Your Local Installer</span>
    <h1>Glass Curtains Estepona</h1>
    <p>Costa Glass is the only glass curtain manufacturer based in Estepona. We manufacture, deliver and install your glass curtains from our local factory — no middlemen, no long lead times.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn-white">Get a Local Quote</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why local matters -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>Your Local Glass Curtain Specialist in Estepona</h2>
    <p>There is a real practical advantage to choosing a manufacturer based in the same town as your property. Costa Glass operates from a purpose-built manufacturing facility in Estepona's industrial zone, less than 3 kilometres from the Old Town and seafront. When you commission glass curtains from us in Estepona, your panels are manufactured locally, transported less than 5 minutes to your address, and installed by the same technicians who built them.</p>
    <p>This means shorter lead times, faster response to any post-installation queries, and a team that understands the specific conditions of Estepona properties — the Levante wind exposure on the eastern side of town, the salt-air challenge for properties on the Paseo Marítimo, and the architecture of both the historic old town buildings and the modern urbanisations along the New Golden Mile towards San Pedro.</p>
    <p>Whether you have a beach apartment on Playa de la Rada, a townhouse in La Resina Golf, or a villa in Finca Cortesin's vicinity, Costa Glass has completed installations in every type of Estepona property and understands what works best in each context.</p>

    <div class="info-strip">
      <div class="info-strip-item"><h3>Factory Location</h3><p>Estepona Industrial Zone</p></div>
      <div class="info-strip-item"><h3>Lead Time (Estepona)</h3><p>3–4 weeks from order</p></div>
      <div class="info-strip-item"><h3>Site Survey</h3><p>Free — same week</p></div>
      <div class="info-strip-item"><h3>Language</h3><p>English & Spanish</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Nearby projects -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>Estepona Glass Curtain Projects</h2>
    <p>Our Estepona portfolio spans all property types and sizes. Here are some examples of our recent work in the area.</p>

    <ul class="advantage-list">
      <li>
        <span class="icon">🏢</span>
        <div class="text">
          <strong>Paseo Marítimo Apartments</strong>
          <p>Multiple sea-facing apartments on Estepona's seafront promenade glazed with 8mm frameless glass curtains in the communal terrace scheme. Our team coordinated work in multiple identical units, allowing the community to approve a uniform appearance across the building.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="icon">🏡</span>
        <div class="text">
          <strong>Selwo Hills Villas</strong>
          <p>Hillside villas with large L-shaped terraces enclosed with 10mm glass curtains plus a bioclimatic pergola covering the main terrace area. The combination creates a usable outdoor-indoor space for 10+ months of the year.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="icon">🍴</span>
        <div class="text">
          <strong>Restaurant Terraces — Old Town</strong>
          <p>Multiple restaurant terraces in the Casco Antiguo fitted with glass curtains and zip screens to extend the outdoor dining season. The installations comply with Estepona's heritage zone regulations.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="icon">🏊</span>
        <div class="text">
          <strong>New Golden Mile Urbanisations</strong>
          <p>Community-wide installations coordinating 15–40 identical terrace enclosures across new-build developments, ensuring uniform façade appearance and simplified community approval.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Service coverage -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>Service Coverage from Estepona</h2>
    <p>From our Estepona base, Costa Glass covers all areas of the Costa del Sol — east towards Marbella and Málaga city, and west towards San Roque, La Línea de la Concepción, and Gibraltar. Same-day site surveys are available within a 20-kilometre radius of Estepona. Extended coverage with 1–2 days lead time for all other areas in Málaga province.</p>
    <p>If you are coordinating a renovation project at your Spanish property from abroad, we are experienced in working with absent owners. Our process includes a detailed video survey call, digital quotation with photos and plans, and regular WhatsApp updates during fabrication and installation. Many of our Estepona clients are British or German property owners who manage the entire process remotely and arrive to find the glass curtains already installed and waiting.</p>

    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/en/glass-curtains-marbella">Glass Curtains Marbella →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/en/glass-curtains-costa-del-sol">Glass Curtains — Full Costa del Sol →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/cortinas-de-cristal">View Our Glass Curtain Products →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-band">
  <h2>Glass Curtains in Estepona — Get Your Local Quote</h2>
  <p>Call, WhatsApp or email us for a free quote. As the local Estepona manufacturer, we can often carry out a site survey the same week you contact us.</p>
  <a href="/contact" class="btn-white">Contact Us in Estepona</a>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
